        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 3:30PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 330 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Orange, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Mineral around 410 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Pendleton, Louisa
Airport, Fredericks Hall, Green Springs, Byrd Mill, Trevilians, Wares
Crossroads, Vawter Corner, Cuckoo, and Gordonsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
